  "name": "Change alternate patient id",
  "version": "HL7 v2.3",
  "chapter": "Patient Administration",
  "description": "An A48 event is used to signal a change of an incorrectly assigned alternate patient identifier value. The “incorrect source alternate patient ID” value is stored in the MRG segment (MRG-2-prior alternate patient ID) and is to be changed to the “correct target alternate patient ID” value stored in the PID segment (PID-4alternate patient ID-PID). \n\nA change has been done at the alternate patient identifier level. That is, a PID-4-alternate patient ID has been found to be incorrect and has been changed.",
